Korean Supplement Guide 🇰🇷🛍️🛒

Dude I’ve never bought as many supplements at once as I have in Seoul. The supplement choices in Seoul are ENDLESS - Koreans believe that beauty comes from the inside and that means you gotta make sure everything else inside is great!

These are some popular ones. Of the types of supplements, collagen is definitely the top, followed by glutathione and milk thistle!!!

Here’s a quick summary if you don’t want it read:

💦 PSTN The All Care Collagen
Best for: All-round beauty glow seeker

🍸 PSTN The Liverthione
Best for: Party girla who need to detox 😜

🐟 PSTN The Omega3 Ultimate
Best for: Banish that brain fog and inflammation

🌸 NQNA GLA-3000 Dream
Best for: Hormonal acne and PMS struggles

🍵 Vital Beautie Meta Green Slim Up
Best for: Cut fat + reduce bloat

💎 Healthy Place Double Toning White Liposome Glutathione
Best for: To brighten and reduce pigmentation

🧘 Donghwa Pharmaceutical MGLab Stress Relief
Best for: Stressed girlies who can’t catch a break (or sleep)

💫 Vital Beautie Super Retinol C
Best for: Anti-aging without the skincare

🍷 BB Lab Pomegranate Collagen S
Best for: Beauty girl on the go, easy to consume collagen jelly sachets

🦠 Foodology Coleology Cut Pro
Best for: Hot girls who have gut issues

〰️ 

Anyway, everyone has their own brand they swear by but these are what were introduced to me and they work really good! I’ve been not only seeing improvements in skin health but overall 😆 And they are affordable compared to what I pay in Singapore so give them a go? 😉

latestPosts.caption:
You can never tear me apart from the Japanese drugstore… even when I’m not in Japan. Thank goodness for #WelciaWishlist season and all the sales so I can get all my faves at wallets-friendly prices! 😋😋

- @canmakesg Moon Glow Highlighter

This is new! And it’s popular for giving that from within luminance unlike other highlighters where it’s obviously sparkly) ⭐️

- @canmakesg Mellow Dew Lip Essence

I was eyeing this in Japan but it was COMPLETELY SOLD OUT when I was there! I’m so glad @teenibeautysg brought it over heheh 🫣

- @suncut_official Multi Vitamin UV Mist

ALSO a NEW LAUNCH! ✨ Mists make reapplication so easy and this one has added vitamins to help with sunburn and pigmentation.

- @countryandstreamsg Honey Nail Treatment Oil

I’m super rough with my hands and I almost never have naked nails so my fingers could use some TLC… and Country & Stream makes the best drugstore hand care products!

- @botanist.singapore Smooth Shampoo and Treatment

I’ve always wanted to bring some back from Japan but I always run out of space before that haha. Super light refreshing formula with no sulfates!

- @canmakesg Creamy Touch Liner

RESTOCKED more of my fave eyeliner

- @canmakesg Plump Lip Care Scrub

Helps with crusty lips and easy to carry around and use! 🫦😋

- @bioliss_official Botanical Bangs Repair Powder

Oily bangs will be the death of me. Luckily handy products like this exist to help with that! Guess that’s how Japanese girlies have the most immaculate bangs 🤠

〰️

You’ll want to head over to @welciasg Northpoint for big discounts UP TO 50% right now and snag some of these so you don’t need to go to Japan! 😬

🌟 PRO-TIP: most things at duty-free end up being even cheaper than Olive Young. I make it a point to not buy immediately and to check the prices on duty-free first, then I order ONLINE and pick it up when I’m at the airport 😉 (plus the BIGGEST BENEFIT is that it doesn’t add to luggage limits too!!! So you can buy more nonsense)

I find that Shinsegae duty free usually has the best deals on skincare but I check Lotte/Shilla/Hyundai JUST TO BE SURE! 😬🙏
